snippet.textDisplay:
Dear MKBHD,
The H in Huawei is a hard H. A lot of YouTubers pronounce it as "Wah-Wei" but it's actually pronounced "Hwah-Wei" just like its written. The first Chinese character of the word Huawei is 华 "hua", meaning "flower" (see their company logo) and it has a hard H sound. Its a small nitpick but it drives me a little crazy each time I hear it. I haven't seen a phone review that pronounces it correctly yet and I'm guessing its probably because no one has told you/corrected you.
Anyway, cheers for all the great content. Stay safe
snippet.textOriginal:

Its a small nitpick but it drives me a little crazy each time I hear it.
